        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 2:25AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 224 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a developing, strong
thunderstorm near Angier, or near Lillington, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Smithfield, Lillington, Angier, Benson, Erwin, Coats, Four Oaks,
Coats Crossroads, and Buies Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
